<TEXT>
from the day that donald t regan moved from 
head man at merrill lynch to secretary of the treasury in the 
reagan cabinet the world war ii combat veteran found the white 
house to be alien territory 
regans gruff marine corps manner had served him well on wall 
street but failed to help him survive the political battleground of 
washington or his conflicts with a determined first lady 
when i was chief executive and i said jump people said 
how high he recalled shortly after coming to washington in 
1981 when he said the same thing as treasury secretary he added 
people asked well do you have an environmental impact 
statement what do you mean by high 
nevertheless regan quickly made his mark winning the 
presidents praise as a very fine salesman for the taxcutting 
policies that were a hallmark of the reagan administration 
in 1985 regan and james a baker iii then the white house 
chief of staff got reagans approval to switch jobs 
as a former marine corps colonel and wall street star he 
fancied the view from the bosss elbow michael k deaver who 
had been bakers deputy later wrote 
once don regan took over as chief of staff there was only one 
man in charge larry speakes then the chief white house 
spokesman recalls in his recent book 
the early reports were glowing said deaver no hint of an 
accident waiting to happen 
troubles soon came however 
when the president underwent cancer surgery in july 1985 regan 
aroused first lady nancy reagans ire by ordering a white house 
helicopter to fly him to bethesda naval hospital according to 
speakes account he decided after a telephone call from mrs 
reagan that he would go by automobile as she did 
after reagans prostate operation the following year the first 
lady and the chief of staff again found themselves at odds she 
thought he was scheduling her husband for too much activity too 
early in his recovery 
then came the revelations that the administration had sold arms 
to iran while seeking freedom for american hostages and that some 
of the money had been funneled to help the contra rebels in 
nicaragua 
when the presidential board headed by former sen john tower 
made its report on the controversy in february 1987 it found 
regan responsible for the chaos that descended upon the white 
house 
he as much as anyone should have insisted that an orderly 
process be preserved the board said 
regan protested does a bank president know whether a bank 
teller is fiddling around with the books no 
this however was not the world of finance but the world of 
washington politics 
the capital quickly sensed that regan was on the way out and 
there were widely believed reports that mrs reagan was helping him 
on his way 
the end came on feb 27 1987 when reagan chose former senate 
republican leader howard h baker jr of tennessee as his new chief 
of staff 
regan hearing the news from thennational security adviser 
frank carlucci who had seen it on a cable news network broadcast 
responded with a onesentence letter of resignation 
now 15 months and many sentences later regan is giving his 
side of the story in his book for the record from wall street to 
washington 
the book being published monday reveals that mrs reagan used 
astrology to determine the timing of the presidents speeches and 
travel 
once again judging from the presidents reaction regan may 
have chosen the wrong adversary 
i would have preferred it if hed decided to attack me 
reagan said friday and apparently from what we hear hes chosen 
to attack my wife and i dont look kindly upon that at all 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

