life or in the massachusetts governorship 
there has been some unmistakable gloom and doom in the 
democratic party psyche but it was the upbeat candidates dukakis 
and jesse jackson who survived the 1988 primaries and dukakis 
isnt likely to make it easy for bush to pin the carter malaise on 
him 
the best america is yet to come he says after running down 
what he sees as the shortcomings of the reagan years were 
going to build a future of hope and pride and opportunity 
still bush wont stop 
it all sounds like jimmy carter reborn again for the third 
