jesse jackson will probably challenge the 
seating of delegates at the democratic convention in july because 
it appears party officials will not act on his objections to the 
selection process his campaign chairman says 
willie brown speaker of the california assembly said he and 
other jackson advisers have spoken to democratic national committee 
chairman paul kirk and other party leaders about jacksons 
insistence that the delegate totals roughly correspond to the 
popular vote 
but those talks brown said are not so far productive and 
the campaign will likely make challenges to the delegate slates of 
states where it believes the selection has been unfair 
i think we are going to end up having to make them because i 
dont think its the discussion going to be productive brown 
told the associated press on saturday 
