sikhs inside the golden temple opened 
fire today on nearby government security posts police said 
setting off a gun battle in which two civilians died and five 
paramilitary troops were injured 
the sikh extremists began firing automatic rifles at 115 pm 
and the troops returned fire with light machine guns according to 
police superintendent baldev singh the fighting continued for at 
least three hours 
singh said it was not known if any militants where killed or 
injured in the exchange 
the civilians killed in the crossfire outside the golden temple 
complex were identified by police as venod kumar 30 a hindu who 
worked with the red cross and dilip kaur an 80yearold sikh 
