<TEXT>
science fiction author robert a heinlein 
whose stranger in a strange land is one of the classics of the 
genre has died at his home at the age of 80 
his death was announced today by the monterey county coroners 
office 
heinlein who moved to this small tourist community recently 
died on sunday according to the coroners office 
the cause of death was not known 
heinlein wrote more than 45 books some of which were turned 
into movies and received science fictions highest awards 
including the hugo 
born in butler mo heinlein graduated from the us naval 
academy in 1929 and served for five years including time on the 
carrier uss lexington then worked in other fields before beginning 
a writing career that saw him become one of the most popular and 
prolific writers of science fiction 
heinlein won numerous awards for his novels and short stories 
written in a simple spare matteroffact style that made them 
popular with both children and adults 
he won the best science fiction novel award from the world 
science fiction convention in 1956 1959 1961 and 1966 the nebula 
award from the science fiction writers of america in 1975 and an 
unprecedented four hugo awards in 1956 for double star in 
1959 for starship troopers in 1961 for stranger in a strange 
land and in 1966 for the moon is a harsh mistress 
other works include the green hills of earth the door 
into summer methusalahs childen puppet masters and 
job a comedy of justice 
heinlein held postgraduate degrees in physics and mathematics 
from the university of california at los angeles and served as an 
aviation engineer for the navy during world war ii as an engineer 
he wrote a number of nonfiction technical books and articles 
a strong supporter of the military throughout his life heinlein 
was a guest commentator during the apollo 11 lunar landing in 1969 
although he was politically conservative heinleins stranger 
in a strange land published in 1961 became one of the 
countercultures handbooks its hero alien valentine smith became 
a symbol of the hope for universal amity for his ability to 
harmonize or grok readily with humans 
heinlein is survived by his wife virginia the couple had no 
children 
</TEXT>
