<TEXT>
argentinas mostwanted military 
fugitive cashiered army gen carlos suarez mason came home in 
handcuffs monday to face 39 murder charges linked to argentinas 
dirty war against leftists 
extradited by a us district court in california the balding 
stocky exgeneral arrived aboard a regular flight of aerolineas 
argentinas the argentine airline from new york 
the plane was stopped 300 yards from the airport terminal and 
suarez mason dressed in grey slacks a sweater and white tennis 
shoes was removed and placed aboard an armored prisonertransport 
vehicle 
escorted by three police cars an armored car and an ambulance 
the exgeneral was taken first to federal police headquarters in 
downtown buenos aires then removed to a special topsecurity jail 
and finally placed in a small cell reserved for prisoners facing 
trial at the somber federal court building 
federal prosecutor luis moreno ocampo said suarez mason 64 
would be held in isolation there until questioning later this 
week by federal judges 
we also have to wait for the official translation of the 
sentence dictated by us judge lowell jensen who ordered suarez 
masons extradition on april 27 after 15 months of hearings in san 
francisco moreno ocampo said 
he said i am going to request a life sentence the 
maximum and he will be sentenced to life 
moreno ocampo predicted the trial could begin in late july or 
the beginning of august 
jensen ruled that suarz mason who fled argentina in 1984 and 
was arrested by us marshals in january 1987 in a san francicco 
suburb could be tried in argentina on charges of 39 murders 
allegedly conducted by troops under his command 
argentina supporting its case with 1600 pages of documents 
had sought suarez masons extradition on 43 charges of murder as 
well as other crimes he had been accused in argentina in 635 
separate cases of human rights violations as well as 
misappropriation of more than 2 million in government funds 
the us judge rejected four of the murder charges ruling that 
identification of the victims was inadequate approved a charge of 
forging a passport renewal and also rejected 23 kidnapping 
charges saying the fiveyear legal deadline for filing the charges 
had expired in 1984 
under extradition law suarez mason can be tried only on charges 
for which extradition was approved 
suarez masons trial had been personally ordered by president 
raul alfonsin shortly after the civilian president took office in 
december 1983 ending nearly eight years of rightist military rule 
the former commander of the buenos airesbased 1st army corps 
was stripped of rank and pension in april 1984 after being 
declared in rebellion for ignoring repeated summonses to appear 
for questioning in connection with the abduction torture and 
murder of suspected leftists in the late 1970s 
a governmentappointed commission has reported that at least 
9000 argentines disappeared in the dirty war against leftist 
subversives waged by the armed forces regime that seized power in 
1976 after ousting former president isabel peron 
from 1976 to 1978 suarez mason commanded the 1st corps in 
whose area more than half of the disappearances took place then he 
was named head of the joint chief of staff 
when he retired in 1981 he was named president of the huge 
state oil monopoly yacimientos petroliferos fiscales a post he 
held until 1982 
the misappropriation of government funds charge is linked to 
suarez masons period as head of the oil company 
in other trials ordered by alfonsin five former ruling junta 
members including two expresidents were convicted in december 
1985 of human rights offenses and sentenced to prison terms ranging 
from life to four years they now are serving their terms at a 
military prison 
the argentine congress last may approved a socalled law of 
due obedience which absolved most of the more than 300 military 
officers from trial on rights abuse charges on grounds that they 
were following orders from superiors the law did not absolve 
highranking officers who directed the antisubversive campaign 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

