<TEXT>
ambassador arthur davis ordered his 
chartered panamanian plane to leave a civilian airport and fly to a 
us air base because he was concerned for his safety the us 
embassy said monday 
it said davis made the decision sunday afternoon when he saw 
panamanian security men arguing with his own security detail after 
the plane landed at the small civilian paitilla airport 
it was a judgment call an embassy statement said the 
ambassadors security detail made the judgment that the situation 
at paitilla was not a good environment 
maj pascual gonzalez director of the panamanian civil 
aeronautics board called it a hijacking incident he said us 
officials refused to provide any information about the plane after 
it landed at howard air base in the former panama canal zone about 
five miles from panama city 
it was the second apparent attempt by panamanian security to 
interfere with the ambassadors movements on april 3 a military 
vehicle tried to stop his limousine as he left the vatican 
ambassadors residence 
relations between the united states and panama have been 
difficult since the reagan administration began supporting efforts 
to oust gen manuel antonio noriega as commander of the defense 
forces and the power behind the civilian government 
a federal court in florida indicted noriega in february on drug 
trafficking charges 
after noriega had the legislature dismiss president eric arturo 
delvalle on feb 26 the united states began imposing financial 
sanctions on panama delvalle had tried to fire the general as 
military commander the day before the united states still 
recognizes delvalle as president 
banks began cashing checks and permitting withdrawals monday for 
the first time in more than two months with strict limits on the 
amount to be taken out of an account 
no withdrawals had been allowed since march 3 longer at some 
banks because of runs on deposits and cash shortages new rules 
limit withdrawals from checking accounts to 25 percent of the march 
3 balance to a maximum of 10000 
some banks began taking deposits april 18 and performing some 
other operations a week later 
gonzalez director of the aeronautics board told a news 
conference procedures were required for a civilian aircraft to 
land at a military base and spend the night there he said the 
plane chartered by the embassy group a sixseat piper did not 
follow them 
the embassy statement said the ambassador considered it an 
emergency and ordered the pilot to take off from the civilian 
airport for nearby howard 
embassy officials would not say who else was on the plane davis 
and his party were returning from a day at the contadora resort 
island 
according to gonzalez others on the plane included gabriel 
lewis galindo jr soninlaw of delvalle who is in hiding in 
panama and the son of an opposition leader 
he said the incident started when airport security personnel saw 
four armed men on the restricted grounds he said airport 
security questioned them and identified them as us citizens 
it was then that the plane landed he said adding that 
embassy security men talked to the ambassador on the radio and the 
plane took off 
the embassy said panamanian security men were armed with m16 
rifles and shotguns demanded passports and other documents and 
their manner was considered hostile 
as far as we are concerned until we conclude the 
investigation the plane was hijacked or stolen gonzalez said 
the planes owner hugo giraud attended the news conference 
with the major and said the embassy had not informed him his plane 
was at howard 
a us embassy official said the aircraft remained there because 
a new flight plan must be filed before it could be flown out 
</TEXT>
