<TEXT>
an earthquake shook jamaica shortly 
before noon monday rocking buildings in kingston and sending 
frightened residents fleeing into the street 
there were no reports of deaths and police said only one injury 
was reported 
they said natalie thompson 14 suffered broken ankles when she 
jumped in panic from the second floor of the rosemount school in 
linstead st catherine 40 miles northwest of the capital of 
kingston 
officials said they had no reports of significant structural 
damage but the office of disaster preparedness is conducting an 
islandwide survey of bridges and buildings 
the seismic research unit at the university of the west indies 
recorded the quake at 1124 am edt and said its center was in 
the caribbean sea about 75 miles northeast of montego bay and 15 
miles south of the cuban communities of pilon and portillo 
it said the earthquake measured 42 degrees on the richter scale 
the university said the worst earthquake recorded in jamaica was 
on jan 14 1907 when kingston was virtually destroyed more than 
1000 people were killed and 9000 were left homeless 
the richter scale is a gauge of energy released by a quake as 
recored on seismographs a tremor registering 4 is capable of 
causing moderate damage and one with a magnitude of 5 can cause 
considerable damage a quake recorded at 7 is considered a major 
quake 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

