<DOCNO> AP880509-0169 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
foreign minister shimon peres of israel 
said monday the soviet union and sovietbloc countries could play 
an increasing role in the search for peace in the middle east 
he came to madrid to attend a meeting of the council of the 
socialist international after stopping off in italy on his flight 
from hungary on monday 
his weekend visit to hungary was unexpected and was the first by 
a top israeli official to that communist state 
peres told reporters in madrid the position of the soviet bloc 
is becoming more and more important in the peace process 
he met in budapest sunday with prime minister karoly grosz 
foreign minister peter varkonyi and janos berecz secretary of the 
hungarian communist partys central committee 
an official at the israeli embassy in madrid who spoke on 
condition of anonymity said it would not be surprising for 
peres to hold talks with soviet observers attending the socialist 
international meeting 
peres and foreign minister guilo andreotti of italy discussed 
the mideast situation in a 50minute meeting at the military 
airport in milan 
the two also discussed the arab uprising in the israelioccupied 
west bank and gaza strip 
they later met briefly with reporters andreotti said italy 
supports the idea of an international middle east peace conference 
he also said that while italy maintains friendly ties with israel 
it supports the palestinian cause 
yossi beilin directorgeneral of israels foreign ministry 
accompanied peres to hungary beilin said upon his return to 
jerusalem monday that hungary is interested in expanding its 
economic ties with the jewish state 
hungary along with all other sovietbloc countries except 
romania cut diplomatic ties with israel following the 1967 middle 
east war but last year the two countries established lowlevel 
diplomatic relations 
israels foreign ministry said in jerusalem without elaboration 
that the peres party and the hungarian leaders discussed the middle 
east conflict and hungarianisraeli ties including economic issues 
and tourism 
i think that this visit conducted upon hungarys initiative 
raises our bilateral ties to another level beilin said on israel 
television 
but he did not predict a full renewal of diplomatic ties 
peres said in madrid that the visit of us secretary of state 
george shultz to the middle east in june is positive for the 
peace process but its significance depends on the outcome of the 
may 27 summit between president reagan and soviet leader mikhail 
gorbachev in moscow 
peres head of israels socialist labor party is to leave 
wednesday for a working trip to washington that will include talks 
with shultz 
