pope john paul ii began a tour of south 
americas poorest country monday with an appeal to its people not 
to lose hope 
i will spend five days among you sharing your aspirations 
seeing firsthand this nation stricken by poverty and a lack of 
development and resources he said in an arrival speech at the la 
paz airport which is 13150 feet above sea level and ringed by 
snowcapped andean peaks 
president victor paz estenssoro said in a welcoming speech the 
visit would help bolster the flagging spirits of bolivians 
you come at a time when bolivia is suffering bitter tests that 
could weaken its spirit or perhaps sink it into a state of 
desperation the 80yearold president said 
he said technological and scientific advances had heightened 
aspirations of the third world without providing the means to 
fulfill them the bolivian people have perhaps been more harshly 
punished than most in this respect he said 
thousands of people including many peasants in colorful indian 
