tin mining center of oruro devastated by mine closures to the 
lowland boom town of santa cruz a center of cattle ranching 
agriculture and cocaine trafficking 
government austerity measures eliminated an annual inflation 
rate of 20000 percent in bolivia but they caused serious labor 
unrest because of mass layoffs the country is also a major source 
of coca leaves the raw material for cocaine 
this visit is the popes tour ninth to latin america since he 
became head of the 860millionmember roman catholic church nearly 
10 years ago he has made 37 pilgrimages abroad from the vatican 
john paul is scheduled to spend his 68th birthday in paraguay on 
may 18 
