for all children he said the civil rights challenge of the 1990s 
was to ensure equal intellectual opportunity in school 
he was an unapologetic defender of reagan efforts to slash the 
federal education budget arguing that more money did not guarantee 
better results and that state and local school budgets were rising 
inexorably anyway 
bennett has been a peripatetic cabinet officer visiting nearly 
100 elementary and secondary schools he has also proven a big draw 
as an afterdinner speaker on the republican fundraising circuit 
bennett who switched from the democratic to the republican 
party two years ago has spoken at 63 gop functions in the past 
three years according to the trade publication education week 
there has been speculation that bennett may eventually run for 
office possibly from his adopted state of north carolina 
