<TEXT>
ford motor co which earned industryrecord 
profits in 1987 and in the first quarter of 1988 is hiring new 
workers for the first time since the layoffs of the early 1980s a 
trade journal reported monday 
in addition ford is using hiring techniques learned from 
foreign automakers who have us factories methods that include 
intense testing screening and interviewing automotive news 
reported 
the socalled transplants mazda motor co nissan motor corp 
toyota motor corp and mitsubishi motors corp factories in the 
united states take as many as 100000 applications to fill 2000 
openings 
ford which laid off about 69000 workers at the beginning of 
the decade has only about 2000 remaining on indefinite layoff 
the others were recalled or dropped off the recall rolls after 
several years 
in recent months we have in certain locations been able to 
hire new people because even these 2000 people with recall rights 
are limited by certain restrictions to plants in their area ford 
spokesman tom foote told the associated press 
its on a small scale just a smattering here and there he 
said its been going on for a few months 
the latest hiring process takes about a month a big change from 
practices of the past when a worker hired friday was put on the 
assembly line monday new workers are put up in a hotel and given a 
week of orientation by the company and the union 
william novotny time standards representative at united auto 
workers local 879 at fords twin cities truck plant in st paul 
minn said it represents a totally new way of hiring 
at the twin cities plant about 50 workers will be chosen from 
among 2000 applicants novotny said about 150 workers already 
have been hired at the plant most of whom have never worked in an 
auto plant said local 879 chairman doug knight 
the new workers include former teachers and members of the 
military 
some of the applicants not selected were children of current 
workers who failed drug tests novotny said drug use is one of the 
biggest problems in auto plants although few union officials want 
to discuss it publicly 
that has caused some heartbreak novotny said but it will 
make a better work place in the long run 
in addition to twin cities ford also has been hiring at its 
wixom assembly plant which builds the lincoln town car and 
continental at its climate control division plant in plymouth and 
at its plastic products division plant in milan those three plants 
are outside detroit 
the hiring has been prompted by new uaw contract rules that 
allow workers who took jobs at other plants to return to their home 
plants as openings occur when they leave ford often has to hire 
new workers to replace them 
by comparison general motors corp the nations largest 
automaker is doing no new hiring because it still has 60000 
workers on indefinite layoff and is shrinking some of its 
operations 
chrysler corp has at least 8000 workers on indefinite layoff 
</TEXT>
