<TEXT>
international business machines corp said 
monday it had produced the first fully functioning computer chips 
to have features measuring just a half micron across 
the microscopically compact chips were made for the defense 
department by ibms federal systems facility in manassas va the 
company said they will be used for such things as capturing and 
processing radar and sonar signals 
this is a significant technological milestone for ibm and the 
us department of defense william gianopulos laboratory 
director of ibm in manassas said in a news release 
ibm is leading the pack sonny maynard the director of the 
defense departments very high speed integrated circuit program 
said in the release 
honeywell inc and trw inc the other two companies that have 
defense contracts to develop halfmicron chips have not completed 
theirs yet trw spokesman timothy dolan said the company was on 
schedule toward a september 1989 deadline on its selfhealing 
super chip which will have about 4 million transistors 
compared to about 100000 for ibms chip 
honeywell spokeswoman susan eich said her company was also on 
schedule 
compact chips run faster because the electricity has less 
distance to travel a micron is onemillionth of a meter or about 
onehundredth the thickness of a sheet of typing paper 
ibms contract with the pentagon restricts how ibm can use the 
halfmicron technology for its commercial products spokesman mark 
root said 
chip companies such as intel corp and advanced micro devices 
inc are planning new fabrication lines for halfmicron chips 
according to scott hudson a market research analyst for integrated 
circuit engineering corp in scottsdale ariz 
this is what all the semiconductor makers are shooting for 
hudson said 
</TEXT>
