chrysler corp announced a buyer incentive 
campaign on monday offering rebates of up to 1500 on several 
models and cutrate financing 
chrysler has used aggressive incentive campaigns and pricing 
strategies throughout the year in an attempt to increase its sales 
the incentives announced monday include 400 rebates on the 1987 
and 1988 plymouth reliant and dodge aries the kcars which already 
are being marketed as lowpriced america series models 
instead of rebates buyers may choose financing ranging from 58 
percent annually on 48month loans and 98 percent on 60month 
loans on eagle premier chrysler offered 88 percent financing for 
up to 72 months 
chrysler is offering a 500 rebate on 1987 and 1988 plymouth 
sundancedodge shadow subcompacts imported dodge and plymouth colt 
subcompacts and the sporty dodge daytona 
